Null checks should not be used with "instanceof"
Why is this an issue? Thereâ€™s no need to null test in conjunction with an instanceof test. null is not an instanceof anything, so a null check is redundant. 
### Noncompliant
if (x != null && x instanceof MyClass) { ... }  // Noncompliant

if (x == null || ! x instanceof MyClass) { ... } // Noncompliant
### Compliant
if (x instanceof MyClass) { ... }

if (! x instanceof MyClass) { ... }
### Noncompliant
{{BUGGY}}
### Compliant
